June 13, 1966. No. 27,

Original.

Ohio v. Kentucky. William B. Saxbe, Attorney General of Ohio, and Robert M. Duncan for plaintiff on the motion. Robert Matthews, Attorney General of Kentucky, and John B. Browning, Assistant Attorney General, for defendant in opposition.

The motion for leave to file bill of complaint granted and the Commonwealth of Kentucky is allowed sixty days to answer.
